.SH NAME
Linux::Event::Scheduler \- Internal monotonic timer queue for Linux::Event::Reactor
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
\&\f(CW\*(C`Linux::Event::Scheduler\*(C'\fR is the internal deadline queue used by the reactor.
It stores callbacks keyed by monotonic nanosecond deadlines and returns expired
items in deadline order.
.PP
This module is internal. Its API is documented only to explain the structure of
this distribution, not as a stable user\-facing contract.
.SH METHODS
.IX Header "METHODS"
.ie n .SS "new(clock => $clock)"
.el .SS "new(clock => \f(CW$clock\fP)"
.IX Subsection "new(clock => $clock)"
Create a scheduler bound to a clock object that provides \f(CW\*(C`now_ns\*(C'\fR and
\&\f(CW\*(C`deadline_in_ns\*(C'\fR.
.ie n .SS "after_ns($delta_ns, $cb)"
.el .SS "after_ns($delta_ns, \f(CW$cb\fP)"
.IX Subsection "after_ns($delta_ns, $cb)"
Schedule a callback relative to the current time.
.ie n .SS "at_ns($deadline_ns, $cb)"
.el .SS "at_ns($deadline_ns, \f(CW$cb\fP)"
.IX Subsection "at_ns($deadline_ns, $cb)"
Schedule a callback for an absolute monotonic deadline.
.SS cancel($id)
.IX Subsection "cancel($id)"
Cancel an existing timer by id.
.SS next_deadline_ns
.IX Subsection "next_deadline_ns"
Return the next live deadline, if any.
.SS pop_expired
.IX Subsection "pop_expired"
Return all expired entries as \f(CW\*(C`[ $id, $cb, $deadline_ns ]\*(C'\fR tuples.
